
[1]prodigally

   PROD'IGALLY, adv. With profusion of expenses; extravagantly; lavishly;
   wastefully; as an estate prodigally dissipated.

   1. With liberal abundance; profusely.

   Nature not bounteous now, but lavish grows,

   Out paths with flow'rs she prodigally strows.
     __________________________________________________________________

